data.description: Charming end unit condominium in the Peninsula that offers a low-maintenance lifestyle with some great amenities! Here are some key points about the property:Location: Situated in a convenient location near Mount Pleasant, Daniel Island, and Charleston, providing easy access to various shopping centers and amenities with a growing community. Property Features: Single-story condo with luxury vinyl plank flooring for easy maintenance. vaulted ceiling in the great room, adding a sense of spaciousness. Recently updated kitchen with microwave, electric range, dishwasher and newer refrigerator. Screened side porch overlooking a wooded buffer for added privacy. Patio area suitable for grilling and an outside storage closet for beach gear and added storage. The backyard has a privacy fence,enhancing the sense of privacy. Two dedicated parking spots are conveniently located in front of the unit. One of the two neighborhood pools is located across the street.  From Nelliefield Plantation, there is a cut-through for the Phillip Simmons schools so kids can walk or ride their bikes to school without going on the main roads.  A $1,300 Lender Credit is available and will be applied towards the buyer's closing costs and pre-paids if the buyer chooses to use the seller's preferred lender.  This credit is in addition to any negotiated seller concessions.
